  <dashboards>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 1'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='900' maxwidth='1500' minheight='900' minwidth='1500' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='55000' id='3' name='Monthly Hours by Number of Projects' w='96333' x='333' y='222' />
        <zone h='50889' id='5' name='Number of Projects Histogram' w='44400' x='333' y='55667' />
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='48556' id='7' type-v2='text' w='54000' x='45467' y='57778'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#e15759' fontsize='10'>INSIGHTS</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>It might be natural that people who work on more projects would also work longer hours.However, a few things stand out from this plot.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>1. Two groups of </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'>employees left: (A) those who worked much less than peers—possibly fired or already exiting, and (B) those who worked much more—likely high contributors who quit. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>2. Everyone with seven projects left the company, and the interquartile ranges of this group and those who left with six projects was ~255 to 295 hours/month, much more than any other group. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>3. The </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'>optimal number of projects for employees to work on seems to be 3 - 4</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>. The ratio of left/stayed is very small for these cohorts.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>4. If you assume a work week of 40 hours and two weeks of vacation per year, then the average number of working hours per month of employees working Monday to Friday = 50 weeks * 40 hours per week / 12 months = 166.67 hours per month. This means that, aside from the employees who worked on two projects, every group, even those who didn&apos;t leave the company worked considerably more hours than this. </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'>It seems that employees here are overworked</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>You can confirm that all employees with seven projects left.</run>
          </formatted-text>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='1' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone h='7111' id='8' name='Monthly Hours by Number of Projects' pane-specification-id='8' param='[federated.09onw4n18ceu1b1dz2kx20464naf].[:Measure Names]' type-v2='color' w='4800' x='94400' y='6333' />
