      <style />
      <size maxheight='900' maxwidth='1500' minheight='900' minwidth='1500' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='50222' id='3' name='Monthly Hours by Satisfaction Level' w='50400' x='267' y='444' />
        <zone h='50111' id='5' name='Monthly Hours by Last Evaluation Score' w='47800' x='51267' y='444' />
        <zone h='8444' id='4' name='Monthly Hours by Satisfaction Level' pane-specification-id='0' param='[federated.09onw4n18ceu1b1dz2kx20464naf].[none:left:ok]' type-v2='color' w='3867' x='96200' y='333' />
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='35778' id='6' type-v2='text' w='42867' x='54800' y='51444'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#e15759' fontsize='10'>INSIGHTS</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>The following observations can be made from the scatterplot above:</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>1. The scatterplot indicates two groups of employees who left: overworked employees who performed very well and employees who worked slightly under the nominal monthly average of 166.67 hours with lower evaluation scores. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>2. There seems to be a correlation between hours worked and evaluation score. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>3. There isn&apos;t a high percentage of employees in the upper left quadrant of this plot; but </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'>working long hours doesn&apos;t guarantee a good evaluation score.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>4.</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'> Most of the employees in this company work well over 167 hours per month.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='34889' id='7' type-v2='text' w='48933' x='1933' y='53444'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#e15759' fontsize='10'>INSIGHTS</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>The following observations can be made from the scatterplot above:</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>1. The scatterplot above shows that there was a sizeable group of employees who worked ~240-315 hours per month. 315 hours per month is over 75 hours per week for a whole year. It&apos;s likely this is related to their satisfaction levels being close to zero. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>2. The plot also shows another group of people who left, those who had more normal working hours. Even so, their satisfaction was only around 0.4. It&apos;s difficult to speculate about why they might have left. It&apos;s possible they felt pressured to work more, considering so many of their peers worked more. And that pressure could have lowered their satisfaction levels. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>3. Finally, there is a group who worked ~210-280 hours per month, and they had satisfaction levels ranging ~0.7-0.9. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
